2734 SingletonPredictionContext.prototype.toString = function() {
2735 	var up = this.parentCtx === null ? "" : this.parentCtx.toString();
2736 	if (up.length === 0) {
2737 		if (this.returnState === PredictionContext.EMPTY_RETURN_STATE) {
2738 			return "$";
2739 		} else {
2740 			return "" + this.returnState;
2741 		}
2742 	} else {
2743 		return "" + this.returnState + " " + up;
2744 	}

2777 function ArrayPredictionContext(parents, returnStates) {
2778 	// Parent can be null only if full ctx mode and we make an array
2779 	// from {@link //EMPTY} and non-empty. We merge {@link //EMPTY} by using
2780 	// null parent and
2781 	// returnState == {@link //EMPTY_RETURN_STATE}.
2782 	var h = new Hash();
2783 	h.update(parents, returnStates);
2784 	var hashCode = h.finish();
2785 	PredictionContext.call(this, hashCode);
2786 	this.parents = parents;
2787 	this.returnStates = returnStates;
2788 	return this;
2789 }

2791 ArrayPredictionContext.prototype = Object.create(PredictionContext.prototype);
2792 ArrayPredictionContext.prototype.constructor = ArrayPredictionContext;
2793 
2794 ArrayPredictionContext.prototype.isEmpty = function() {
2795 	// since EMPTY_RETURN_STATE can only appear in the last position, we
2796 	// don't need to verify that size==1
2797 	return this.returnStates[0] === PredictionContext.EMPTY_RETURN_STATE;
2798 };

2814 ArrayPredictionContext.prototype.equals = function(other) {
2815 	if (this === other) {
2816 		return true;
2817 	} else if (!(other instanceof ArrayPredictionContext)) {
2818 		return false;
2819 	} else if (this.hashCode() !== other.hashCode()) {
2820 		return false; // can't be same if hash is different
2821 	} else {
2822 		return this.returnStates === other.returnStates &&
2823 				this.parents === other.parents;
2824 	}
2825 };

2827 ArrayPredictionContext.prototype.toString = function() {
2828 	if (this.isEmpty()) {
2829 		return "[]";
2830 	} else {
2831 		var s = "[";
2832 		for (var i = 0; i < this.returnStates.length; i++) {
2833 			if (i > 0) {
2834 				s = s + ", ";
2835 			}
2836 			if (this.returnStates[i] === PredictionContext.EMPTY_RETURN_STATE) {
2837 				s = s + "$";
2838 				continue;
2839 			}
2840 			s = s + this.returnStates[i];
2841 			if (this.parents[i] !== null) {
2842 				s = s + " " + this.parents[i];
2843 			} else {
2844 				s = s + "null";
2845 			}
2846 		}
2847 		return s + "]";
2848 	}
2849 };

2851 // Convert a {@link RuleContext} tree to a {@link PredictionContext} graph.
2852 // Return {@link //EMPTY} if {@code outerContext} is empty or null.
2853 // /
2854 function predictionContextFromRuleContext(atn, outerContext) {
2855 	if (outerContext === undefined || outerContext === null) {
2856 		outerContext = RuleContext.EMPTY;
2857 	}
2858 	// if we are in RuleContext of start rule, s, then PredictionContext
2859 	// is EMPTY. Nobody called us. (if we are empty, return empty)
2860 	if (outerContext.parentCtx === null || outerContext === RuleContext.EMPTY) {
2861 		return PredictionContext.EMPTY;
2862 	}
2863 	// If we have a parent, convert it to a PredictionContext graph
2864 	var parent = predictionContextFromRuleContext(atn, outerContext.parentCtx);
2865 	var state = atn.states[outerContext.invokingState];
2866 	var transition = state.transitions[0];
2867 	return SingletonPredictionContext.create(parent, transition.followState.stateNumber);
2868 }
2869 /* 
2870 function calculateListsHashString(parents, returnStates) { 
2871     var s = ""; 
2872     parents.map(function(p) { 
2873         s = s + p; 
2874     }); 
2875     returnStates.map(function(r) { 
2876         s = s + r; 
2877     }); 
2878     return s; 
2879 } 
2880 */
2881 function merge(a, b, rootIsWildcard, mergeCache) {
2882 	// share same graph if both same
2883 	if (a === b) {
2884 		return a;
2885 	}
2886 	if (a instanceof SingletonPredictionContext && b instanceof SingletonPredictionContext) {
2887 		return mergeSingletons(a, b, rootIsWildcard, mergeCache);
2888 	}
2889 	// At least one of a or b is array
2890 	// If one is $ and rootIsWildcard, return $ as// wildcard
2891 	if (rootIsWildcard) {
2892 		if (a instanceof EmptyPredictionContext) {
2893 			return a;
2894 		}
2895 		if (b instanceof EmptyPredictionContext) {
2896 			return b;
2897 		}
2898 	}
2899 	// convert singleton so both are arrays to normalize
2900 	if (a instanceof SingletonPredictionContext) {
2901 		a = new ArrayPredictionContext([a.getParent()], [a.returnState]);
2902 	}
2903 	if (b instanceof SingletonPredictionContext) {
2904 		b = new ArrayPredictionContext([b.getParent()], [b.returnState]);
2905 	}
2906 	return mergeArrays(a, b, rootIsWildcard, mergeCache);
2907 }
2908 
2909 //
2910 // Merge two {@link SingletonPredictionContext} instances.
2911 //
2912 // <p>Stack tops equal, parents merge is same; return left graph.<br>
2913 // <embed src="images/SingletonMerge_SameRootSamePar.svg"
2914 // type="image/svg+xml"/></p>
2915 //
2916 // <p>Same stack top, parents differ; merge parents giving array node, then
2917 // remainders of those graphs. A new root node is created to point to the
2918 // merged parents.<br>
2919 // <embed src="images/SingletonMerge_SameRootDiffPar.svg"
2920 // type="image/svg+xml"/></p>
2921 //
2922 // <p>Different stack tops pointing to same parent. Make array node for the
2923 // root where both element in the root point to the same (original)
2924 // parent.<br>
2925 // <embed src="images/SingletonMerge_DiffRootSamePar.svg"
2926 // type="image/svg+xml"/></p>
2927 //
2928 // <p>Different stack tops pointing to different parents. Make array node for
2929 // the root where each element points to the corresponding original
2930 // parent.<br>
2931 // <embed src="images/SingletonMerge_DiffRootDiffPar.svg"
2932 // type="image/svg+xml"/></p>
2933 //
2934 // @param a the first {@link SingletonPredictionContext}
2935 // @param b the second {@link SingletonPredictionContext}
2936 // @param rootIsWildcard {@code true} if this is a local-context merge,
2937 // otherwise false to indicate a full-context merge
2938 // @param mergeCache
2939 // /
2940 function mergeSingletons(a, b, rootIsWildcard, mergeCache) {
2941 	if (mergeCache !== null) {
2942 		var previous = mergeCache.get(a, b);
2943 		if (previous !== null) {
2944 			return previous;
2945 		}
2946 		previous = mergeCache.get(b, a);
2947 		if (previous !== null) {
2948 			return previous;
2949 		}
2950 	}
2951 
2952 	var rootMerge = mergeRoot(a, b, rootIsWildcard);
2953 	if (rootMerge !== null) {
2954 		if (mergeCache !== null) {
2955 			mergeCache.set(a, b, rootMerge);
2956 		}
2957 		return rootMerge;
2958 	}
2959 	if (a.returnState === b.returnState) {
2960 		var parent = merge(a.parentCtx, b.parentCtx, rootIsWildcard, mergeCache);
2961 		// if parent is same as existing a or b parent or reduced to a parent,
2962 		// return it
2963 		if (parent === a.parentCtx) {
2964 			return a; // ax + bx = ax, if a=b
2965 		}
2966 		if (parent === b.parentCtx) {
2967 			return b; // ax + bx = bx, if a=b
2968 		}
2969 		// else: ax + ay = a'[x,y]
2970 		// merge parents x and y, giving array node with x,y then remainders
2971 		// of those graphs. dup a, a' points at merged array
2972 		// new joined parent so create new singleton pointing to it, a'
2973 		var spc = SingletonPredictionContext.create(parent, a.returnState);
2974 		if (mergeCache !== null) {
2975 			mergeCache.set(a, b, spc);
2976 		}
2977 		return spc;
2978 	} else { // a != b payloads differ
2979 		// see if we can collapse parents due to $+x parents if local ctx
2980 		var singleParent = null;
2981 		if (a === b || (a.parentCtx !== null && a.parentCtx === b.parentCtx)) { // ax +
2982 																				// bx =
2983 																				// [a,b]x
2984 			singleParent = a.parentCtx;
2985 		}
2986 		if (singleParent !== null) { // parents are same
2987 			// sort payloads and use same parent
2988 			var payloads = [ a.returnState, b.returnState ];
2989 			if (a.returnState > b.returnState) {
2990 				payloads[0] = b.returnState;
2991 				payloads[1] = a.returnState;
2992 			}
2993 			var parents = [ singleParent, singleParent ];
2994 			var apc = new ArrayPredictionContext(parents, payloads);
2995 			if (mergeCache !== null) {
2996 				mergeCache.set(a, b, apc);
2997 			}
2998 			return apc;
2999 		}
3000 		// parents differ and can't merge them. Just pack together
3001 		// into array; can't merge.
3002 		// ax + by = [ax,by]
3003 		var payloads = [ a.returnState, b.returnState ];
3004 		var parents = [ a.parentCtx, b.parentCtx ];
3005 		if (a.returnState > b.returnState) { // sort by payload
3006 			payloads[0] = b.returnState;
3007 			payloads[1] = a.returnState;
3008 			parents = [ b.parentCtx, a.parentCtx ];
3009 		}
3010 		var a_ = new ArrayPredictionContext(parents, payloads);
3011 		if (mergeCache !== null) {
3012 			mergeCache.set(a, b, a_);
3013 		}
3014 		return a_;
3015 	}
3016 }
3017 
3018 //
3019 // Handle case where at least one of {@code a} or {@code b} is
3020 // {@link //EMPTY}. In the following diagrams, the symbol {@code $} is used
3021 // to represent {@link //EMPTY}.
3022 //
3023 // <h2>Local-Context Merges</h2>
3024 //
3025 // <p>These local-context merge operations are used when {@code rootIsWildcard}
3026 // is true.</p>
3027 //
3028 // <p>{@link //EMPTY} is superset of any graph; return {@link //EMPTY}.<br>
3029 // <embed src="images/LocalMerge_EmptyRoot.svg" type="image/svg+xml"/></p>
3030 //
3031 // <p>{@link //EMPTY} and anything is {@code //EMPTY}, so merged parent is
3032 // {@code //EMPTY}; return left graph.<br>
3033 // <embed src="images/LocalMerge_EmptyParent.svg" type="image/svg+xml"/></p>
3034 //
3035 // <p>Special case of last merge if local context.<br>
3036 // <embed src="images/LocalMerge_DiffRoots.svg" type="image/svg+xml"/></p>
3037 //
3038 // <h2>Full-Context Merges</h2>
3039 //
3040 // <p>These full-context merge operations are used when {@code rootIsWildcard}
3041 // is false.</p>
3042 //
3043 // <p><embed src="images/FullMerge_EmptyRoots.svg" type="image/svg+xml"/></p>
3044 //
3045 // <p>Must keep all contexts; {@link //EMPTY} in array is a special value (and
3046 // null parent).<br>
3047 // <embed src="images/FullMerge_EmptyRoot.svg" type="image/svg+xml"/></p>
3048 //
3049 // <p><embed src="images/FullMerge_SameRoot.svg" type="image/svg+xml"/></p>
3050 //
3051 // @param a the first {@link SingletonPredictionContext}
3052 // @param b the second {@link SingletonPredictionContext}
3053 // @param rootIsWildcard {@code true} if this is a local-context merge,
3054 // otherwise false to indicate a full-context merge
3055 // /
3056 function mergeRoot(a, b, rootIsWildcard) {
3057 	if (rootIsWildcard) {
3058 		if (a === PredictionContext.EMPTY) {
3059 			return PredictionContext.EMPTY; // // + b =//
3060 		}
3061 		if (b === PredictionContext.EMPTY) {
3062 			return PredictionContext.EMPTY; // a +// =//
3063 		}
3064 	} else {
3065 		if (a === PredictionContext.EMPTY && b === PredictionContext.EMPTY) {
3066 			return PredictionContext.EMPTY; // $ + $ = $
3067 		} else if (a === PredictionContext.EMPTY) { // $ + x = [$,x]
3068 			var payloads = [ b.returnState,
3069 					PredictionContext.EMPTY_RETURN_STATE ];
3070 			var parents = [ b.parentCtx, null ];
3071 			return new ArrayPredictionContext(parents, payloads);
3072 		} else if (b === PredictionContext.EMPTY) { // x + $ = [$,x] ($ is always first if present)
3073 			var payloads = [ a.returnState, PredictionContext.EMPTY_RETURN_STATE ];
3074 			var parents = [ a.parentCtx, null ];
3075 			return new ArrayPredictionContext(parents, payloads);
3076 		}
3077 	}
3078 	return null;
3079 }
3080 
3081 //
3082 // Merge two {@link ArrayPredictionContext} instances.
3083 //
3084 // <p>Different tops, different parents.<br>
3085 // <embed src="images/ArrayMerge_DiffTopDiffPar.svg" type="image/svg+xml"/></p>
3086 //
3087 // <p>Shared top, same parents.<br>
3088 // <embed src="images/ArrayMerge_ShareTopSamePar.svg" type="image/svg+xml"/></p>
3089 //
3090 // <p>Shared top, different parents.<br>
3091 // <embed src="images/ArrayMerge_ShareTopDiffPar.svg" type="image/svg+xml"/></p>
3092 //
3093 // <p>Shared top, all shared parents.<br>
3094 // <embed src="images/ArrayMerge_ShareTopSharePar.svg"
3095 // type="image/svg+xml"/></p>
3096 //
3097 // <p>Equal tops, merge parents and reduce top to
3098 // {@link SingletonPredictionContext}.<br>
3099 // <embed src="images/ArrayMerge_EqualTop.svg" type="image/svg+xml"/></p>
3100 // /
3101 function mergeArrays(a, b, rootIsWildcard, mergeCache) {
3102 	if (mergeCache !== null) {
3103 		var previous = mergeCache.get(a, b);
3104 		if (previous !== null) {
3105 			return previous;
3106 		}
3107 		previous = mergeCache.get(b, a);
3108 		if (previous !== null) {
3109 			return previous;
3110 		}
3111 	}
3112 	// merge sorted payloads a + b => M
3113 	var i = 0; // walks a
3114 	var j = 0; // walks b
3115 	var k = 0; // walks target M array
3116 
3117 	var mergedReturnStates = [];
3118 	var mergedParents = [];
3119 	// walk and merge to yield mergedParents, mergedReturnStates
3120 	while (i < a.returnStates.length && j < b.returnStates.length) {
3121 		var a_parent = a.parents[i];
3122 		var b_parent = b.parents[j];
3123 		if (a.returnStates[i] === b.returnStates[j]) {
3124 			// same payload (stack tops are equal), must yield merged singleton
3125 			var payload = a.returnStates[i];
3126 			// $+$ = $
3127 			var bothDollars = payload === PredictionContext.EMPTY_RETURN_STATE &&
3128 					a_parent === null && b_parent === null;
3129 			var ax_ax = (a_parent !== null && b_parent !== null && a_parent === b_parent); // ax+ax
3130 																							// ->
3131 																							// ax
3132 			if (bothDollars || ax_ax) {
3133 				mergedParents[k] = a_parent; // choose left
3134 				mergedReturnStates[k] = payload;
3135 			} else { // ax+ay -> a'[x,y]
3136 				var mergedParent = merge(a_parent, b_parent, rootIsWildcard, mergeCache);
3137 				mergedParents[k] = mergedParent;
3138 				mergedReturnStates[k] = payload;
3139 			}
3140 			i += 1; // hop over left one as usual
3141 			j += 1; // but also skip one in right side since we merge
3142 		} else if (a.returnStates[i] < b.returnStates[j]) { // copy a[i] to M
3143 			mergedParents[k] = a_parent;
3144 			mergedReturnStates[k] = a.returnStates[i];
3145 			i += 1;
3146 		} else { // b > a, copy b[j] to M
3147 			mergedParents[k] = b_parent;
3148 			mergedReturnStates[k] = b.returnStates[j];
3149 			j += 1;
3150 		}
3151 		k += 1;
3152 	}
3153 	// copy over any payloads remaining in either array
3154 	if (i < a.returnStates.length) {
3155 		for (var p = i; p < a.returnStates.length; p++) {
3156 			mergedParents[k] = a.parents[p];
3157 			mergedReturnStates[k] = a.returnStates[p];
3158 			k += 1;
3159 		}
3160 	} else {
3161 		for (var p = j; p < b.returnStates.length; p++) {
3162 			mergedParents[k] = b.parents[p];
3163 			mergedReturnStates[k] = b.returnStates[p];
3164 			k += 1;
3165 		}
3166 	}
3167 	// trim merged if we combined a few that had same stack tops
3168 	if (k < mergedParents.length) { // write index < last position; trim
3169 		if (k === 1) { // for just one merged element, return singleton top
3170 			var a_ = SingletonPredictionContext.create(mergedParents[0],
3171 					mergedReturnStates[0]);
3172 			if (mergeCache !== null) {
3173 				mergeCache.set(a, b, a_);
3174 			}
3175 			return a_;
3176 		}
3177 		mergedParents = mergedParents.slice(0, k);
3178 		mergedReturnStates = mergedReturnStates.slice(0, k);
3179 	}
3180 
3181 	var M = new ArrayPredictionContext(mergedParents, mergedReturnStates);
3182 
3183 	// if we created same array as a or b, return that instead
3184 	// TODO: track whether this is possible above during merge sort for speed
3185 	if (M === a) {
3186 		if (mergeCache !== null) {
3187 			mergeCache.set(a, b, a);
3188 		}
3189 		return a;
3190 	}
3191 	if (M === b) {
3192 		if (mergeCache !== null) {
3193 			mergeCache.set(a, b, b);
3194 		}
3195 		return b;
3196 	}
3197 	combineCommonParents(mergedParents);
3198 
3199 	if (mergeCache !== null) {
3200 		mergeCache.set(a, b, M);
3201 	}
3202 	return M;
3203 }
3204 
3205 //
3206 // Make pass over all <em>M</em> {@code parents}; merge any {@code equals()}
3207 // ones.
3208 // /
3209 function combineCommonParents(parents) {
3210 	var uniqueParents = {};
3211 
3212 	for (var p = 0; p < parents.length; p++) {
3213 		var parent = parents[p];
3214 		if (!(parent in uniqueParents)) {
3215 			uniqueParents[parent] = parent;
3216 		}
3217 	}
3218 	for (var q = 0; q < parents.length; q++) {
3219 		parents[q] = uniqueParents[parents[q]];
3220 	}
3221 }
3222 
3223 function getCachedPredictionContext(context, contextCache, visited) {
3224 	if (context.isEmpty()) {
3225 		return context;
3226 	}
3227 	var existing = visited[context] || null;
3228 	if (existing !== null) {
3229 		return existing;
3230 	}
3231 	existing = contextCache.get(context);
3232 	if (existing !== null) {
3233 		visited[context] = existing;
3234 		return existing;
3235 	}
3236 	var changed = false;
3237 	var parents = [];
3238 	for (var i = 0; i < parents.length; i++) {
3239 		var parent = getCachedPredictionContext(context.getParent(i), contextCache, visited);
3240 		if (changed || parent !== context.getParent(i)) {
3241 			if (!changed) {
3242 				parents = [];
3243 				for (var j = 0; j < context.length; j++) {
3244 					parents[j] = context.getParent(j);
3245 				}
3246 				changed = true;
3247 			}
3248 			parents[i] = parent;
3249 		}
3250 	}
3251 	if (!changed) {
3252 		contextCache.add(context);
3253 		visited[context] = context;
3254 		return context;
3255 	}
3256 	var updated = null;
3257 	if (parents.length === 0) {
3258 		updated = PredictionContext.EMPTY;
3259 	} else if (parents.length === 1) {
3260 		updated = SingletonPredictionContext.create(parents[0], context
3261 				.getReturnState(0));
3262 	} else {
3263 		updated = new ArrayPredictionContext(parents, context.returnStates);
3264 	}
3265 	contextCache.add(updated);
3266 	visited[updated] = updated;
3267 	visited[context] = updated;
3268 
3269 	return updated;
3270 }
3271 
3272 // ter's recursive version of Sam's getAllNodes()
3273 function getAllContextNodes(context, nodes, visited) {
3274 	if (nodes === null) {
3275 		nodes = [];
3276 		return getAllContextNodes(context, nodes, visited);
3277 	} else if (visited === null) {
3278 		visited = {};
3279 		return getAllContextNodes(context, nodes, visited);
3280 	} else {
3281 		if (context === null || visited[context] !== null) {
3282 			return nodes;
3283 		}
3284 		visited[context] = context;
3285 		nodes.push(context);
3286 		for (var i = 0; i < context.length; i++) {
3287 			getAllContextNodes(context.getParent(i), nodes, visited);
3288 		}
3289 		return nodes;
3290 	}
3291 }

3387 // How should a token be displayed in an error message? The default
3388 //  is to display just the text, but during development you might
3389 //  want to have a lot of information spit out.  Override in that case
3390 //  to use t.toString() (which, for CommonToken, dumps everything about
3391 //  the token). This is better than forcing you to override a method in
3392 //  your token objects because you don't have to go modify your lexer
3393 //  so that it creates a new Java type.
3394 //
3395 // @deprecated This method is not called by the ANTLR 4 Runtime. Specific
3396 // implementations of {@link ANTLRErrorStrategy} may provide a similar
3397 // feature when necessary. For example, see
3398 // {@link DefaultErrorStrategy//getTokenErrorDisplay}.

3400 Recognizer.prototype.getTokenErrorDisplay = function(t) {
3401     if (t===null) {
3402         return "<no token>";
3403     }
3404     var s = t.text;
3405     if (s===null) {
3406         if (t.type===Token.EOF) {
3407             s = "<EOF>";
3408         } else {
3409             s = "<" + t.type + ">";
3410         }
3411     }
3412     s = s.replace("\n","\\n").replace("\r","\\r").replace("\t","\\t");
3413     return "'" + s + "'";
3414 };

3456 //  A rule context is a record of a single rule invocation. It knows
3457 //  which context invoked it, if any. If there is no parent context, then
3458 //  naturally the invoking state is not valid.  The parent link
3459 //  provides a chain upwards from the current rule invocation to the root
3460 //  of the invocation tree, forming a stack. We actually carry no
3461 //  information about the rule associated with this context (except
3462 //  when parsing). We keep only the state number of the invoking state from
3463 //  the ATN submachine that invoked this. Contrast this with the s
3464 //  pointer inside ParserRuleContext that tracks the current state
3465 //  being "executed" for the current rule.
3466 //
3467 //  The parent contexts are useful for computing lookahead sets and
3468 //  getting error information.
3469 //
3470 //  These objects are used during parsing and prediction.
3471 //  For the special case of parsers, we use the subclass
3472 //  ParserRuleContext.
3473 //
3474 //  @see ParserRuleContext
3475 ///
3476

3482 function RuleContext(parent, invokingState) {
3483 	RuleNode.call(this);
3484 	// What context invoked this rule?
3485 	this.parentCtx = parent || null;
3486 	// What state invoked the rule associated with this context?
3487 	// The "return address" is the followState of invokingState
3488 	// If parent is null, this should be -1.
3489 	this.invokingState = invokingState || -1;
3490 	return this;
3491 }

3503 	return n;

3616 // A token has properties: text, type, line, character position in the line
3617 // (so we can ignore tabs), token channel, index, and source from which
3618 // we obtained this token.

3620 function Token() {
3621 	this.source = null;
3622 	this.type = null; // token type of the token
3623 	this.channel = null; // The parser ignores everything not on DEFAULT_CHANNEL
3624 	this.start = null; // optional; return -1 if not implemented.
3625 	this.stop = null; // optional; return -1 if not implemented.
3626 	this.tokenIndex = null; // from 0..n-1 of the token object in the input stream
3627 	this.line = null; // line=1..n of the 1st character
3628 	this.column = null; // beginning of the line at which it occurs, 0..n-1
3629 	this._text = null; // text of the token.
3630 	return this;
3631 }

3679 function CommonToken(source, type, channel, start, stop) {
3680 	Token.call(this);
3681 	this.source = source !== undefined ? source : CommonToken.EMPTY_SOURCE;
3682 	this.type = type !== undefined ? type : null;
3683 	this.channel = channel !== undefined ? channel : Token.DEFAULT_CHANNEL;
3684 	this.start = start !== undefined ? start : -1;
3685 	this.stop = stop !== undefined ? stop : -1;
3686 	this.tokenIndex = -1;
3687 	if (this.source[0] !== null) {
3688 		this.line = source[0].line;
3689 		this.column = source[0].column;
3690 	} else {
3691 		this.column = -1;
3692 	}
3693 	return this;
3694 }

3703 // Constructs a new {@link CommonToken} as a copy of another {@link Token}.
3704 //
3705 // <p>
3706 // If {@code oldToken} is also a {@link CommonToken} instance, the newly
3707 // constructed token will share a reference to the {@link //text} field and
3708 // the {@link Pair} stored in {@link //source}. Otherwise, {@link //text} will
3709 // be assigned the result of calling {@link //getText}, and {@link //source}
3710 // will be constructed from the result of {@link Token//getTokenSource} and
3711 // {@link Token//getInputStream}.</p>
3712 //
3713 // @param oldToken The token to copy.
3714 //
3715 CommonToken.prototype.clone = function() {
3716 	var t = new CommonToken(this.source, this.type, this.channel, this.start,
3717 			this.stop);
3718 	t.tokenIndex = this.tokenIndex;
3719 	t.line = this.line;
3720 	t.column = this.column;
3721 	t.text = this.text;
3722 	return t;
3723 };

3725 Object.defineProperty(CommonToken.prototype, "text", {
3726 	get : function() {
3727 		if (this._text !== null) {
3728 			return this._text;
3729 		}
3730 		var input = this.getInputStream();
3731 		if (input === null) {
3732 			return null;
3733 		}
3734 		var n = input.size;
3735 		if (this.start < n && this.stop < n) {
3736 			return input.getText(this.start, this.stop);
3737 		} else {
3738 			return "<EOF>";
3739 		}
3740 	},
3741 	set : function(text) {
3742 		this._text = text;
3743 	}
3744 });

3747 	var txt = this.text;
3748 	if (txt !== null) {
3749 		txt = txt.replace(/\n/g, "\\n").replace(/\r/g, "\\r").replace(/\t/g, "\\t");
3750 	} else {
3751 		txt = "<no text>";
3752 	}
3753 	return "[@" + this.tokenIndex + "," + this.start + ":" + this.stop + "='" +
3754 			txt + "',<" + this.type + ">" +
3755 			(this.channel > 0 ? ",channel=" + this.channel : "") + "," +
3756 			this.line + ":" + this.column + "]";
3757 };

3772 String.prototype.seed = String.prototype.seed || Math.round(Math.random() * Math.pow(2, 32));

3774 String.prototype.hashCode = function () {
3775     var remainder, bytes, h1, h1b, c1, c1b, c2, c2b, k1, i,
3776         key = this.toString();
3777 
3778     remainder = key.length & 3; // key.length % 4
3779     bytes = key.length - remainder;
3780     h1 = String.prototype.seed;
3781     c1 = 0xcc9e2d51;
3782     c2 = 0x1b873593;
3783     i = 0;
3784 
3785     while (i < bytes) {
3786         k1 =
3787             ((key.charCodeAt(i) & 0xff)) |
3788             ((key.charCodeAt(++i) & 0xff) << 8) |
3789             ((key.charCodeAt(++i) & 0xff) << 16) |
3790             ((key.charCodeAt(++i) & 0xff) << 24);
3791         ++i;
3792 
3793         k1 = ((((k1 & 0xffff) * c1) + ((((k1 >>> 16) * c1) & 0xffff) << 16))) & 0xffffffff;
3794         k1 = (k1 << 15) | (k1 >>> 17);
3795         k1 = ((((k1 & 0xffff) * c2) + ((((k1 >>> 16) * c2) & 0xffff) << 16))) & 0xffffffff;
3796 
3797         h1 ^= k1;
3798         h1 = (h1 << 13) | (h1 >>> 19);
3799         h1b = ((((h1 & 0xffff) * 5) + ((((h1 >>> 16) * 5) & 0xffff) << 16))) & 0xffffffff;
3800         h1 = (((h1b & 0xffff) + 0x6b64) + ((((h1b >>> 16) + 0xe654) & 0xffff) << 16));
3801     }
3802 
3803     k1 = 0;
3804 
3805     switch (remainder) {
3806         case 3:
3807             k1 ^= (key.charCodeAt(i + 2) & 0xff) << 16;
3808         case 2:
3809             k1 ^= (key.charCodeAt(i + 1) & 0xff) << 8;
3810         case 1:
3811             k1 ^= (key.charCodeAt(i) & 0xff);
3812 
3813             k1 = (((k1 & 0xffff) * c1) + ((((k1 >>> 16) * c1) & 0xffff) << 16)) & 0xffffffff;
3814             k1 = (k1 << 15) | (k1 >>> 17);
3815             k1 = (((k1 & 0xffff) * c2) + ((((k1 >>> 16) * c2) & 0xffff) << 16)) & 0xffffffff;
3816             h1 ^= k1;
3817     }
3818 
3819     h1 ^= key.length;
3820 
3821     h1 ^= h1 >>> 16;
3822     h1 = (((h1 & 0xffff) * 0x85ebca6b) + ((((h1 >>> 16) * 0x85ebca6b) & 0xffff) << 16)) & 0xffffffff;
3823     h1 ^= h1 >>> 13;
3824     h1 = ((((h1 & 0xffff) * 0xc2b2ae35) + ((((h1 >>> 16) * 0xc2b2ae35) & 0xffff) << 16))) & 0xffffffff;
3825     h1 ^= h1 >>> 16;
3826 
3827     return h1 >>> 0;
3828 };

4092 function Hash() {
4093     this.count = 0;
4094     this.hash = 0;
4095     return this;
4096 }
4097 
4098 Hash.prototype.update = function () {
4099     for(var i=0;i<arguments.length;i++) {
4100         var value = arguments[i];
4101         if (value == null)
4102             continue;
4103         if(Array.isArray(value))
4104             this.update.apply(value);
4105         else {
4106             var k = 0;
4107             switch (typeof(value)) {
4108                 case 'undefined':
4109                 case 'function':
4110                     continue;
4111                 case 'number':
4112                 case 'boolean':
4113                     k = value;
4114                     break;
4115                 case 'string':
4116                     k = value.hashCode();
4117                     break;
4118                 default:
4119                     value.updateHashCode(this);
4120                     continue;
4121             }
4122             k = k * 0xCC9E2D51;
4123             k = (k << 15) | (k >>> (32 - 15));
4124             k = k * 0x1B873593;
4125             this.count = this.count + 1;
4126             var hash = this.hash ^ k;
4127             hash = (hash << 13) | (hash >>> (32 - 13));
4128             hash = hash * 5 + 0xE6546B64;
4129             this.hash = hash;
4130         }
4131     }
4132 }
4133 
4134 Hash.prototype.finish = function () {
4135     var hash = this.hash ^ (this.count * 4);
4136     hash = hash ^ (hash >>> 16);
4137     hash = hash * 0x85EBCA6B;
4138     hash = hash ^ (hash >>> 13);
4139     hash = hash * 0xC2B2AE35;
4140     hash = hash ^ (hash >>> 16);
4141     return hash;
4142 }
4143 
4144 function hashStuff() {
4145     var hash = new Hash();

4147     return hash.finish();
4148 }

4181 function equalArrays(a, b)
4182 {
4183     if (!Array.isArray(a) || !Array.isArray(b))
4184         return false;
4185     if (a == b)
4186         return true;
4187     if (a.length != b.length)
4188         return false;
4189     for (var i = 0; i < a.length; i++) {
4190         if (a[i] == b[i])
4191             continue;
4192         if (!a[i].equals(b[i]))
4193             return false;
4194     }
4195     return true;
4196 };

4249 // Compute the set of valid tokens that can occur starting in state {@code s}.
4250 //  If {@code ctx} is null, the set of tokens will not include what can follow
4251 //  the rule surrounding {@code s}. In other words, the set will be
4252 //  restricted to tokens reachable staying within {@code s}'s rule.
4253 ATN.prototype.nextTokensInContext = function(s, ctx) {
4254     var anal = new LL1Analyzer(this);
4255     return anal.LOOK(s, null, ctx);

4260 // rule.

4262     if (s.nextTokenWithinRule !== null ) {
4263         return s.nextTokenWithinRule;
4264     }
4265     s.nextTokenWithinRule = this.nextTokensInContext(s, null);
4266     s.nextTokenWithinRule.readOnly = true;

4304 // Computes the set of input symbols which could follow ATN state number
4305 // {@code stateNumber} in the specified full {@code context}. This method
4306 // considers the complete parser context, but does not evaluate semantic
4307 // predicates (i.e. all predicates encountered during the calculation are
4308 // assumed true). If a path in the ATN exists from the starting state to the
4309 // {@link RuleStopState} of the outermost context without matching any
4310 // symbols, {@link Token//EOF} is added to the returned set.
4311 //
4312 // <p>If {@code context} is {@code null}, it is treated as
4313 // {@link ParserRuleContext//EMPTY}.</p>
4314 //
4315 // @param stateNumber the ATN state number
4316 // @param context the full parse context
4317 // @return The set of potentially valid input symbols which could follow the
4318 // specified state in the specified context.
4319 // @throws IllegalArgumentException if the ATN does not contain a state with
4320 // number {@code stateNumber}
4321 var Token = require('./../Token').Token;
4322 
4323 ATN.prototype.getExpectedTokens = function( stateNumber, ctx ) {
4324     if ( stateNumber < 0 || stateNumber >= this.states.length ) {
4325         throw("Invalid state number.");
4326     }
4327     var s = this.states[stateNumber];
4328     var following = this.nextTokens(s);
4329     if (!following.contains(Token.EPSILON)) {
4330         return following;
4331     }
4332     var expected = new IntervalSet();
4333     expected.addSet(following);
4334     expected.removeOne(Token.EPSILON);
4335     while (ctx !== null && ctx.invokingState >= 0 && following.contains(Token.EPSILON)) {
4336         var invokingState = this.states[ctx.invokingState];
4337         var rt = invokingState.transitions[0];
4338         following = this.nextTokens(rt.followState);
4339         expected.addSet(following);
4340         expected.removeOne(Token.EPSILON);
4341         ctx = ctx.parentCtx;
4342     }
4343     if (following.contains(Token.EPSILON)) {
4344         expected.addOne(Token.EOF);
4345     }
4346     return expected;
4347 };

4360 // A tuple: (ATN state, predicted alt, syntactic, semantic context).
4361 //  The syntactic context is a graph-structured stack node whose
4362 //  path(s) to the root is the rule invocation(s)

4364 //  the tree of semantic predicates encountered before reaching

4373 function checkParams(params, isCfg) {
4374 	if(params===null) {
4375 		var result = { state:null, alt:null, context:null, semanticContext:null };
4376 		if(isCfg) {
4377 			result.reachesIntoOuterContext = 0;
4378 		}
4379 		return result;
4380 	} else {
4381 		var props = {};
4382 		props.state = params.state || null;
4383 		props.alt = (params.alt === undefined) ? null : params.alt;
4384 		props.context = params.context || null;
4385 		props.semanticContext = params.semanticContext || null;
4386 		if(isCfg) {
4387 			props.reachesIntoOuterContext = params.reachesIntoOuterContext || 0;
4388 			props.precedenceFilterSuppressed = params.precedenceFilterSuppressed || false;
4389 		}
4390 		return props;
4391 	}
4392 }

4394 function ATNConfig(params, config) {
4395 	this.checkContext(params, config);
4396 	params = checkParams(params);
4397 	config = checkParams(config, true);
4398     // The ATN state associated with this configuration///
4399     this.state = params.state!==null ? params.state : config.state;
4400     // What alt (or lexer rule) is predicted by this configuration///
4401     this.alt = params.alt!==null ? params.alt : config.alt;
4402     // The stack of invoking states leading to the rule/states associated
4403     //  with this config.  We track only those contexts pushed during
4404     //  execution of the ATN simulator.
4405     this.context = params.context!==null ? params.context : config.context;
4406     this.semanticContext = params.semanticContext!==null ? params.semanticContext :
4407         (config.semanticContext!==null ? config.semanticContext : SemanticContext.NONE);
4408     // We cannot execute predicates dependent upon local context unless
4409     // we know for sure we are in the correct context. Because there is
4410     // no way to do this efficiently, we simply cannot evaluate
4411     // dependent predicates unless we are in the rule that initially
4412     // invokes the ATN simulator.
4413     //
4414     // closure() tracks the depth of how far we dip into the
4415     // outer context: depth &gt; 0.  Note that it may not be totally
4416     // accurate depth since I don't ever decrement. TODO: make it a boolean then
4417     this.reachesIntoOuterContext = config.reachesIntoOuterContext;
4418     this.precedenceFilterSuppressed = config.precedenceFilterSuppressed;
4419     return this;
4420 }

4422 ATNConfig.prototype.checkContext = function(params, config) {
4423 	if((params.context===null || params.context===undefined) &&
4424 			(config===null || config.context===null || config.context===undefined)) {
4425 		this.context = null;
4426 	}
4427 };

4550 	return c.hashCodeForConfigSet();

4553 function equalATNConfigs(a, b) {
4554 	if ( a===b ) {
4555 		return true;
4556 	} else if ( a===null || b===null ) {
4557 		return false;
4558 	} else
4559        return a.equalsForConfigSet(b);

4563 function ATNConfigSet(fullCtx) {
4564 	//
4565 	// The reason that we need this is because we don't want the hash map to use
4566 	// the standard hash code and equals. We need all configurations with the
4567 	// same
4568 	// {@code (s,i,_,semctx)} to be equal. Unfortunately, this key effectively
4569 	// doubles
4570 	// the number of objects associated with ATNConfigs. The other solution is
4571 	// to
4572 	// use a hash table that lets us specify the equals/hashcode operation.
4573 	// All configs but hashed by (s, i, _, pi) not including context. Wiped out
4574 	// when we go readonly as this set becomes a DFA state.
4575 	this.configLookup = new Set(hashATNConfig, equalATNConfigs);
4576 	// Indicates that this configuration set is part of a full context
4577 	// LL prediction. It will be used to determine how to merge $. With SLL
4578 	// it's a wildcard whereas it is not for LL context merge.
4579 	this.fullCtx = fullCtx === undefined ? true : fullCtx;
4580 	// Indicates that the set of configurations is read-only. Do not
4581 	// allow any code to manipulate the set; DFA states will point at
4582 	// the sets and they must not change. This does not protect the other
4583 	// fields; in particular, conflictingAlts is set after
4584 	// we've made this readonly.
4585 	this.readOnly = false;
4586 	// Track the elements as they are added to the set; supports get(i)///
4587 	this.configs = [];
4588 
4589 	// TODO: these fields make me pretty uncomfortable but nice to pack up info
4590 	// together, saves recomputation
4591 	// TODO: can we track conflicts as they are added to save scanning configs
4592 	// later?
4593 	this.uniqueAlt = 0;
4594 	this.conflictingAlts = null;
4595 
4596 	// Used in parser and lexer. In lexer, it indicates we hit a pred
4597 	// while computing a closure operation. Don't make a DFA state from this.
4598 	this.hasSemanticContext = false;
4599 	this.dipsIntoOuterContext = false;
4600 
4601 	this.cachedHashCode = -1;
4602 
4603 	return this;
4604 }
4605 
4606 // Adding a new config means merging contexts with existing configs for
4607 // {@code (s, i, pi, _)}, where {@code s} is the
4608 // {@link ATNConfig//state}, {@code i} is the {@link ATNConfig//alt}, and
4609 // {@code pi} is the {@link ATNConfig//semanticContext}. We use
4610 // {@code (s,i,pi)} as key.
4611 //
4612 // <p>This method updates {@link //dipsIntoOuterContext} and
4613 // {@link //hasSemanticContext} when necessary.</p>
4614 // /
4615 ATNConfigSet.prototype.add = function(config, mergeCache) {
4616 	if (mergeCache === undefined) {
4617 		mergeCache = null;
4618 	}
4619 	if (this.readOnly) {
4620 		throw "This set is readonly";
4621 	}
4622 	if (config.semanticContext !== SemanticContext.NONE) {
4623 		this.hasSemanticContext = true;
4624 	}
4625 	if (config.reachesIntoOuterContext > 0) {
4626 		this.dipsIntoOuterContext = true;
4627 	}
4628 	var existing = this.configLookup.add(config);
4629 	if (existing === config) {
4630 		this.cachedHashCode = -1;
4631 		this.configs.push(config); // track order here
4632 		return true;
4633 	}
4634 	// a previous (s,i,pi,_), merge with it and save result
4635 	var rootIsWildcard = !this.fullCtx;
4636 	var merged = merge(existing.context, config.context, rootIsWildcard, mergeCache);
4637 	// no need to check for existing.context, config.context in cache
4638 	// since only way to create new graphs is "call rule" and here. We
4639 	// cache at both places.
4640 	existing.reachesIntoOuterContext = Math.max( existing.reachesIntoOuterContext, config.reachesIntoOuterContext);
4641 	// make sure to preserve the precedence filter suppression during the merge
4642 	if (config.precedenceFilterSuppressed) {
4643 		existing.precedenceFilterSuppressed = true;
4644 	}
4645 	existing.context = merged; // replace context; no need to alt mapping
4646 	return true;
4647 };
4648 
4649 ATNConfigSet.prototype.getStates = function() {

4652 		states.add(this.configs[i].state);
4653 	}
4654 	return states;

4660 		var c = this.configs[i].semanticContext;
4661 		if (c !== SemanticContext.NONE) {
4662 			preds.push(c.semanticContext);
4663 		}
4664 	}
4665 	return preds;
4666 };

4682 		var config = this.configs[i];

4715             var hash = new Hash();

4717 			this.cachedHashCode = hash.finish();

4889 function ATNDeserializer (options) {
4890 
4891     if ( options=== undefined || options === null ) {
4892         options = ATNDeserializationOptions.defaultOptions;
4893     }
4894     this.deserializationOptions = options;
4895     this.stateFactories = null;
4896     this.actionFactories = null;

4901 // Determines if a particular serialized representation of an ATN supports
4902 // a particular feature, identified by the {@link UUID} used for serializing
4903 // the ATN at the time the feature was first introduced.
4904 //
4905 // @param feature The {@link UUID} marking the first time the feature was
4906 // supported in the serialized ATN.
4907 // @param actualUuid The {@link UUID} of the actual serialized ATN which is
4908 // currently being deserialized.
4909 // @return {@code true} if the {@code actualUuid} value represents a
4910 // serialized ATN at or after the feature identified by {@code feature} was
4911 // introduced; otherwise, {@code false}.
4912 
4913 ATNDeserializer.prototype.isFeatureSupported = function(feature, actualUuid) {
4914     var idx1 = SUPPORTED_UUIDS.indexOf(feature);
4915     if (idx1<0) {
4916         return false;
4917     }
4918     var idx2 = SUPPORTED_UUIDS.indexOf(actualUuid);
4919     return idx2 >= idx1;
4920 };
4921 
4922 ATNDeserializer.prototype.deserialize = function(data) {
4923     this.reset(data);
4924     this.checkVersion();
4925     this.checkUUID();
4926     var atn = this.readATN();
4927     this.readStates(atn);
4928     this.readRules(atn);
4929     this.readModes(atn);
4930     var sets = [];
4931     // First, deserialize sets with 16-bit arguments <= U+FFFF.
4932     this.readSets(atn, sets, this.readInt.bind(this));
4933     // Next, if the ATN was serialized with the Unicode SMP feature,
4934     // deserialize sets with 32-bit arguments <= U+10FFFF.
4935     if (this.isFeatureSupported(ADDED_UNICODE_SMP, this.uuid)) {
4936         this.readSets(atn, sets, this.readInt32.bind(this));
4937     }
4938     this.readEdges(atn, sets);
4939     this.readDecisions(atn);
4940     this.readLexerActions(atn);
4941     this.markPrecedenceDecisions(atn);
4942     this.verifyATN(atn);
4943     if (this.deserializationOptions.generateRuleBypassTransitions && atn.grammarType === ATNType.PARSER ) {
4944         this.generateRuleBypassTransitions(atn);
4945         // re-verify after modification
4946         this.verifyATN(atn);
4947     }
4948     return atn;
4949 };
4950 
4951 ATNDeserializer.prototype.reset = function(data) {
4952 	var adjust = function(c) {
4953         var v = c.charCodeAt(0);
4954         return v>1  ? v-2 : -1;
4955 	};
4956     var temp = data.split("").map(adjust);
4957     // don't adjust the first value since that's the version number
4958     temp[0] = data.charCodeAt(0);
4959     this.data = temp;
4960     this.pos = 0;
4961 };
4962 
4963 ATNDeserializer.prototype.checkVersion = function() {
4964     var version = this.readInt();
4965     if ( version !== SERIALIZED_VERSION ) {
4966         throw ("Could not deserialize ATN with version " + version + " (expected " + SERIALIZED_VERSION + ").");
4967     }
4968 };
4969 
4970 ATNDeserializer.prototype.checkUUID = function() {
4971     var uuid = this.readUUID();
4972     if (SUPPORTED_UUIDS.indexOf(uuid)<0) {
4973         throw ("Could not deserialize ATN with UUID: " + uuid +
4974                         " (expected " + SERIALIZED_UUID + " or a legacy UUID).", uuid, SERIALIZED_UUID);
4975     }
4976     this.uuid = uuid;
4977 };
4978 
4979 ATNDeserializer.prototype.readATN = function() {
4980     var grammarType = this.readInt();
4981     var maxTokenType = this.readInt();
4982     return new ATN(grammarType, maxTokenType);
4983 };
4984 
4985 ATNDeserializer.prototype.readStates = function(atn) {
4986 	var j, pair, stateNumber;
4987     var loopBackStateNumbers = [];
4988     var endStateNumbers = [];
4989     var nstates = this.readInt();
4990     for(var i=0; i<nstates; i++) {
4991         var stype = this.readInt();
4992         // ignore bad type of states
4993         if (stype===ATNState.INVALID_TYPE) {
4994             atn.addState(null);
4995             continue;
4996         }
4997         var ruleIndex = this.readInt();
4998         if (ruleIndex === 0xFFFF) {
4999             ruleIndex = -1;
5000         }
5001         var s = this.stateFactory(stype, ruleIndex);
5002         if (stype === ATNState.LOOP_END) { // special case
5003             var loopBackStateNumber = this.readInt();
5004             loopBackStateNumbers.push([s, loopBackStateNumber]);
5005         } else if(s instanceof BlockStartState) {
5006             var endStateNumber = this.readInt();
5007             endStateNumbers.push([s, endStateNumber]);
5008         }
5009         atn.addState(s);
5010     }
5011     // delay the assignment of loop back and end states until we know all the
5012 	// state instances have been initialized
5013     for (j=0; j<loopBackStateNumbers.length; j++) {
5014         pair = loopBackStateNumbers[j];
5015         pair[0].loopBackState = atn.states[pair[1]];
5016     }
5017 
5018     for (j=0; j<endStateNumbers.length; j++) {
5019         pair = endStateNumbers[j];
5020         pair[0].endState = atn.states[pair[1]];
5021     }
5022 
5023     var numNonGreedyStates = this.readInt();
5024     for (j=0; j<numNonGreedyStates; j++) {
5025         stateNumber = this.readInt();
5026         atn.states[stateNumber].nonGreedy = true;
5027     }
5028 
5029     var numPrecedenceStates = this.readInt();
5030     for (j=0; j<numPrecedenceStates; j++) {
5031         stateNumber = this.readInt();
5032         atn.states[stateNumber].isPrecedenceRule = true;
5033     }
5034 };
5035 
5036 ATNDeserializer.prototype.readRules = function(atn) {
5037     var i;
5038     var nrules = this.readInt();
5039     if (atn.grammarType === ATNType.LEXER ) {
5040         atn.ruleToTokenType = initArray(nrules, 0);
5041     }
5042     atn.ruleToStartState = initArray(nrules, 0);
5043     for (i=0; i<nrules; i++) {
5044         var s = this.readInt();
5045         var startState = atn.states[s];
5046         atn.ruleToStartState[i] = startState;
5047         if ( atn.grammarType === ATNType.LEXER ) {
5048             var tokenType = this.readInt();
5049             if (tokenType === 0xFFFF) {
5050                 tokenType = Token.EOF;
5051             }
5052             atn.ruleToTokenType[i] = tokenType;
5053         }
5054     }
5055     atn.ruleToStopState = initArray(nrules, 0);
5056     for (i=0; i<atn.states.length; i++) {
5057         var state = atn.states[i];
5058         if (!(state instanceof RuleStopState)) {
5059             continue;
5060         }
5061         atn.ruleToStopState[state.ruleIndex] = state;
5062         atn.ruleToStartState[state.ruleIndex].stopState = state;
5063     }
5064 };
5065 
5066 ATNDeserializer.prototype.readModes = function(atn) {
5067     var nmodes = this.readInt();
5068     for (var i=0; i<nmodes; i++) {
5069         var s = this.readInt();
5070         atn.modeToStartState.push(atn.states[s]);
5071     }
5072 };
5073 
5074 ATNDeserializer.prototype.readSets = function(atn, sets, readUnicode) {
5075     var m = this.readInt();
5076     for (var i=0; i<m; i++) {
5077         var iset = new IntervalSet();
5078         sets.push(iset);
5079         var n = this.readInt();
5080         var containsEof = this.readInt();
5081         if (containsEof!==0) {
5082             iset.addOne(-1);
5083         }
5084         for (var j=0; j<n; j++) {
5085             var i1 = readUnicode();
5086             var i2 = readUnicode();
5087             iset.addRange(i1, i2);
5088         }
5089     }
5090 };
5091 
5092 ATNDeserializer.prototype.readEdges = function(atn, sets) {
5093 	var i, j, state, trans, target;
5094     var nedges = this.readInt();
5095     for (i=0; i<nedges; i++) {
5096         var src = this.readInt();
5097         var trg = this.readInt();
5098         var ttype = this.readInt();
5099         var arg1 = this.readInt();
5100         var arg2 = this.readInt();
5101         var arg3 = this.readInt();
5102         trans = this.edgeFactory(atn, ttype, src, trg, arg1, arg2, arg3, sets);
5103         var srcState = atn.states[src];
5104         srcState.addTransition(trans);
5105     }
5106     // edges for rule stop states can be derived, so they aren't serialized
5107     for (i=0; i<atn.states.length; i++) {
5108         state = atn.states[i];
5109         for (j=0; j<state.transitions.length; j++) {
5110             var t = state.transitions[j];
5111             if (!(t instanceof RuleTransition)) {
5112                 continue;
5113             }
5114 			var outermostPrecedenceReturn = -1;
5115 			if (atn.ruleToStartState[t.target.ruleIndex].isPrecedenceRule) {
5116 				if (t.precedence === 0) {
5117 					outermostPrecedenceReturn = t.target.ruleIndex;
5118 				}
5119 			}
5120 
5121 			trans = new EpsilonTransition(t.followState, outermostPrecedenceReturn);
5122             atn.ruleToStopState[t.target.ruleIndex].addTransition(trans);
5123         }
5124     }
5125 
5126     for (i=0; i<atn.states.length; i++) {
5127         state = atn.states[i];
5128         if (state instanceof BlockStartState) {
5129             // we need to know the end state to set its start state
5130             if (state.endState === null) {
5131                 throw ("IllegalState");
5132             }
5133             // block end states can only be associated to a single block start
5134 			// state
5135             if ( state.endState.startState !== null) {
5136                 throw ("IllegalState");
5137             }
5138             state.endState.startState = state;
5139         }
5140         if (state instanceof PlusLoopbackState) {
5141             for (j=0; j<state.transitions.length; j++) {
5142                 target = state.transitions[j].target;
5143                 if (target instanceof PlusBlockStartState) {
5144                     target.loopBackState = state;
5145                 }
5146             }
5147         } else if (state instanceof StarLoopbackState) {
5148             for (j=0; j<state.transitions.length; j++) {
5149                 target = state.transitions[j].target;
5150                 if (target instanceof StarLoopEntryState) {
5151                     target.loopBackState = state;
5152                 }
5153             }
5154         }
5155     }
5156 };
5157 
5158 ATNDeserializer.prototype.readDecisions = function(atn) {
5159     var ndecisions = this.readInt();
5160     for (var i=0; i<ndecisions; i++) {
5161         var s = this.readInt();
5162         var decState = atn.states[s];
5163         atn.decisionToState.push(decState);
5164         decState.decision = i;
5165     }
5166 };
5167 
5168 ATNDeserializer.prototype.readLexerActions = function(atn) {
5169     if (atn.grammarType === ATNType.LEXER) {
5170         var count = this.readInt();
5171         atn.lexerActions = initArray(count, null);
5172         for (var i=0; i<count; i++) {
5173             var actionType = this.readInt();
5174             var data1 = this.readInt();
5175             if (data1 === 0xFFFF) {
5176                 data1 = -1;
5177             }
5178             var data2 = this.readInt();
5179             if (data2 === 0xFFFF) {
5180                 data2 = -1;
5181             }
5182             var lexerAction = this.lexerActionFactory(actionType, data1, data2);
5183             atn.lexerActions[i] = lexerAction;
5184         }
5185     }
5186 };
5187 
5188 ATNDeserializer.prototype.generateRuleBypassTransitions = function(atn) {
5189 	var i;
5190     var count = atn.ruleToStartState.length;
5191     for(i=0; i<count; i++) {
5192         atn.ruleToTokenType[i] = atn.maxTokenType + i + 1;
5193     }
5194     for(i=0; i<count; i++) {
5195         this.generateRuleBypassTransition(atn, i);
5196     }
5197 };
5198 
5199 ATNDeserializer.prototype.generateRuleBypassTransition = function(atn, idx) {
5200 	var i, state;
5201     var bypassStart = new BasicBlockStartState();
5202     bypassStart.ruleIndex = idx;
5203     atn.addState(bypassStart);
5204 
5205     var bypassStop = new BlockEndState();
5206     bypassStop.ruleIndex = idx;
5207     atn.addState(bypassStop);
5208 
5209     bypassStart.endState = bypassStop;
5210     atn.defineDecisionState(bypassStart);
5211 
5212     bypassStop.startState = bypassStart;
5213 
5214     var excludeTransition = null;
5215     var endState = null;
5216 
5217     if (atn.ruleToStartState[idx].isPrecedenceRule) {
5218         // wrap from the beginning of the rule to the StarLoopEntryState
5219         endState = null;
5220         for(i=0; i<atn.states.length; i++) {
5221             state = atn.states[i];
5222             if (this.stateIsEndStateFor(state, idx)) {
5223                 endState = state;
5224                 excludeTransition = state.loopBackState.transitions[0];
5225                 break;
5226             }
5227         }
5228         if (excludeTransition === null) {
5229             throw ("Couldn't identify final state of the precedence rule prefix section.");
5230         }
5231     } else {
5232         endState = atn.ruleToStopState[idx];
5233     }
5234 
5235     // all non-excluded transitions that currently target end state need to
5236 	// target blockEnd instead
5237     for(i=0; i<atn.states.length; i++) {
5238         state = atn.states[i];
5239         for(var j=0; j<state.transitions.length; j++) {
5240             var transition = state.transitions[j];
5241             if (transition === excludeTransition) {
5242                 continue;
5243             }
5244             if (transition.target === endState) {
5245                 transition.target = bypassStop;
5246             }
5247         }
5248     }
5249 
5250     // all transitions leaving the rule start state need to leave blockStart
5251 	// instead
5252     var ruleToStartState = atn.ruleToStartState[idx];
5253     var count = ruleToStartState.transitions.length;
5254     while ( count > 0) {
5255         bypassStart.addTransition(ruleToStartState.transitions[count-1]);
5256         ruleToStartState.transitions = ruleToStartState.transitions.slice(-1);
5257     }
5258     // link the new states
5259     atn.ruleToStartState[idx].addTransition(new EpsilonTransition(bypassStart));
5260     bypassStop.addTransition(new EpsilonTransition(endState));
5261 
5262     var matchState = new BasicState();
5263     atn.addState(matchState);
5264     matchState.addTransition(new AtomTransition(bypassStop, atn.ruleToTokenType[idx]));
5265     bypassStart.addTransition(new EpsilonTransition(matchState));
5266 };
5267 
5268 ATNDeserializer.prototype.stateIsEndStateFor = function(state, idx) {
5269     if ( state.ruleIndex !== idx) {
5270         return null;
5271     }
5272     if (!( state instanceof StarLoopEntryState)) {
5273         return null;
5274     }
5275     var maybeLoopEndState = state.transitions[state.transitions.length - 1].target;
5276     if (!( maybeLoopEndState instanceof LoopEndState)) {
5277         return null;
5278     }
5279     if (maybeLoopEndState.epsilonOnlyTransitions &&
5280         (maybeLoopEndState.transitions[0].target instanceof RuleStopState)) {
5281         return state;
5282     } else {
5283         return null;
5284     }
5285 };
5286 
5287 //
5288 // Analyze the {@link StarLoopEntryState} states in the specified ATN to set
5289 // the {@link StarLoopEntryState//isPrecedenceDecision} field to the
5290 // correct value.
5291 //
5292 // @param atn The ATN.
5293 //
5294 ATNDeserializer.prototype.markPrecedenceDecisions = function(atn) {
5295 	for(var i=0; i<atn.states.length; i++) {
5296 		var state = atn.states[i];
5297 		if (!( state instanceof StarLoopEntryState)) {
5298             continue;
5299         }
5300         // We analyze the ATN to determine if this ATN decision state is the
5301         // decision for the closure block that determines whether a
5302         // precedence rule should continue or complete.
5303         //
5304         if ( atn.ruleToStartState[state.ruleIndex].isPrecedenceRule) {
5305             var maybeLoopEndState = state.transitions[state.transitions.length - 1].target;
5306             if (maybeLoopEndState instanceof LoopEndState) {
5307                 if ( maybeLoopEndState.epsilonOnlyTransitions &&
5308                         (maybeLoopEndState.transitions[0].target instanceof RuleStopState)) {
5309                     state.isPrecedenceDecision = true;
5310                 }
5311             }
5312         }
5313 	}
5314 };
5315 
5316 ATNDeserializer.prototype.verifyATN = function(atn) {
5317     if (!this.deserializationOptions.verifyATN) {
5318         return;
5319     }
5320     // verify assumptions
5321 	for(var i=0; i<atn.states.length; i++) {
5322         var state = atn.states[i];
5323         if (state === null) {
5324             continue;
5325         }
5326         this.checkCondition(state.epsilonOnlyTransitions || state.transitions.length <= 1);
5327         if (state instanceof PlusBlockStartState) {
5328             this.checkCondition(state.loopBackState !== null);
5329         } else  if (state instanceof StarLoopEntryState) {
5330             this.checkCondition(state.loopBackState !== null);
5331             this.checkCondition(state.transitions.length === 2);
5332             if (state.transitions[0].target instanceof StarBlockStartState) {
5333                 this.checkCondition(state.transitions[1].target instanceof LoopEndState);
5334                 this.checkCondition(!state.nonGreedy);
5335             } else if (state.transitions[0].target instanceof LoopEndState) {
5336                 this.checkCondition(state.transitions[1].target instanceof StarBlockStartState);
5337                 this.checkCondition(state.nonGreedy);
5338             } else {
5339                 throw("IllegalState");
5340             }
5341         } else if (state instanceof StarLoopbackState) {
5342             this.checkCondition(state.transitions.length === 1);
5343             this.checkCondition(state.transitions[0].target instanceof StarLoopEntryState);
5344         } else if (state instanceof LoopEndState) {
5345             this.checkCondition(state.loopBackState !== null);
5346         } else if (state instanceof RuleStartState) {
5347             this.checkCondition(state.stopState !== null);
5348         } else if (state instanceof BlockStartState) {
5349             this.checkCondition(state.endState !== null);
5350         } else if (state instanceof BlockEndState) {
5351             this.checkCondition(state.startState !== null);
5352         } else if (state instanceof DecisionState) {
5353             this.checkCondition(state.transitions.length <= 1 || state.decision >= 0);
5354         } else {
5355             this.checkCondition(state.transitions.length <= 1 || (state instanceof RuleStopState));
5356         }
5357 	}
5358 };
5359 
5360 ATNDeserializer.prototype.checkCondition = function(condition, message) {
5361     if (!condition) {
5362         if (message === undefined || message===null) {
5363             message = "IllegalState";
5364         }
5365         throw (message);
5366     }
5367 };

5369 ATNDeserializer.prototype.readInt = function() {
5370     return this.data[this.pos++];
5371 };

5373 ATNDeserializer.prototype.readInt32 = function() {
5374     var low = this.readInt();
5375     var high = this.readInt();
5376     return low | (high << 16);
5377 };

5379 ATNDeserializer.prototype.readLong = function() {
5380     var low = this.readInt32();
5381     var high = this.readInt32();
5382     return (low & 0x00000000FFFFFFFF) | (high << 32);
5383 };

5385 function createByteToHex() {
5386 	var bth = [];
5387 	for (var i = 0; i < 256; i++) {
5388 		bth[i] = (i + 0x100).toString(16).substr(1).toUpperCase();
5389 	}
5390 	return bth;
5391 }
5392 
5393 var byteToHex = createByteToHex();
5394 
5395 ATNDeserializer.prototype.readUUID = function() {
5396 	var bb = [];
5397 	for(var i=7;i>=0;i--) {
5398 		var int = this.readInt();
5399 		/* jshint bitwise: false */
5400 		bb[(2*i)+1] = int & 0xFF;
5401 		bb[2*i] = (int >> 8) & 0xFF;
5402 	}
5403     return byteToHex[bb[0]] + byteToHex[bb[1]] +
5404     byteToHex[bb[2]] + byteToHex[bb[3]] + '-' +
5405     byteToHex[bb[4]] + byteToHex[bb[5]] + '-' +
5406     byteToHex[bb[6]] + byteToHex[bb[7]] + '-' +
5407     byteToHex[bb[8]] + byteToHex[bb[9]] + '-' +
5408     byteToHex[bb[10]] + byteToHex[bb[11]] +
5409     byteToHex[bb[12]] + byteToHex[bb[13]] +
5410     byteToHex[bb[14]] + byteToHex[bb[15]];
5411 };
5412 
5413 ATNDeserializer.prototype.edgeFactory = function(atn, type, src, trg, arg1, arg2, arg3, sets) {
5414     var target = atn.states[trg];
5415     switch(type) {
5416     case Transition.EPSILON:
5417         return new EpsilonTransition(target);
5418     case Transition.RANGE:
5419         return arg3 !== 0 ? new RangeTransition(target, Token.EOF, arg2) : new RangeTransition(target, arg1, arg2);
5420     case Transition.RULE:
5421         return new RuleTransition(atn.states[arg1], arg2, arg3, target);
5422     case Transition.PREDICATE:
5423         return new PredicateTransition(target, arg1, arg2, arg3 !== 0);
5424     case Transition.PRECEDENCE:
5425         return new PrecedencePredicateTransition(target, arg1);
5426     case Transition.ATOM:
5427         return arg3 !== 0 ? new AtomTransition(target, Token.EOF) : new AtomTransition(target, arg1);
5428     case Transition.ACTION:
5429         return new ActionTransition(target, arg1, arg2, arg3 !== 0);
5430     case Transition.SET:
5431         return new SetTransition(target, sets[arg1]);
5432     case Transition.NOT_SET:
5433         return new NotSetTransition(target, sets[arg1]);
5434     case Transition.WILDCARD:
5435         return new WildcardTransition(target);
5436     default:
5437         throw "The specified transition type: " + type + " is not valid.";
5438     }
5439 };
5440 
5441 ATNDeserializer.prototype.stateFactory = function(type, ruleIndex) {
5442     if (this.stateFactories === null) {
5443         var sf = [];
5444         sf[ATNState.INVALID_TYPE] = null;
5445         sf[ATNState.BASIC] = function() { return new BasicState(); };
5446         sf[ATNState.RULE_START] = function() { return new RuleStartState(); };
5447         sf[ATNState.BLOCK_START] = function() { return new BasicBlockStartState(); };
5448         sf[ATNState.PLUS_BLOCK_START] = function() { return new PlusBlockStartState(); };
5449         sf[ATNState.STAR_BLOCK_START] = function() { return new StarBlockStartState(); };
5450         sf[ATNState.TOKEN_START] = function() { return new TokensStartState(); };
5451         sf[ATNState.RULE_STOP] = function() { return new RuleStopState(); };
5452         sf[ATNState.BLOCK_END] = function() { return new BlockEndState(); };
5453         sf[ATNState.STAR_LOOP_BACK] = function() { return new StarLoopbackState(); };
5454         sf[ATNState.STAR_LOOP_ENTRY] = function() { return new StarLoopEntryState(); };
5455         sf[ATNState.PLUS_LOOP_BACK] = function() { return new PlusLoopbackState(); };
5456         sf[ATNState.LOOP_END] = function() { return new LoopEndState(); };
5457         this.stateFactories = sf;
5458     }
5459     if (type>this.stateFactories.length || this.stateFactories[type] === null) {
5460         throw("The specified state type " + type + " is not valid.");
5461     } else {
5462         var s = this.stateFactories[type]();
5463         if (s!==null) {
5464             s.ruleIndex = ruleIndex;
5465             return s;
5466         }
5467     }
5468 };
5469 
5470 ATNDeserializer.prototype.lexerActionFactory = function(type, data1, data2) {
5471     if (this.actionFactories === null) {
5472         var af = [];
5473         af[LexerActionType.CHANNEL] = function(data1, data2) { return new LexerChannelAction(data1); };
5474         af[LexerActionType.CUSTOM] = function(data1, data2) { return new LexerCustomAction(data1, data2); };
5475         af[LexerActionType.MODE] = function(data1, data2) { return new LexerModeAction(data1); };
5476         af[LexerActionType.MORE] = function(data1, data2) { return LexerMoreAction.INSTANCE; };
5477         af[LexerActionType.POP_MODE] = function(data1, data2) { return LexerPopModeAction.INSTANCE; };
5478         af[LexerActionType.PUSH_MODE] = function(data1, data2) { return new LexerPushModeAction(data1); };
5479         af[LexerActionType.SKIP] = function(data1, data2) { return LexerSkipAction.INSTANCE; };
5480         af[LexerActionType.TYPE] = function(data1, data2) { return new LexerTypeAction(data1); };
5481         this.actionFactories = af;
5482     }
5483     if (type>this.actionFactories.length || this.actionFactories[type] === null) {
5484         throw("The specified lexer action type " + type + " is not valid.");
5485     } else {
5486         return this.actionFactories[type](data1, data2);
5487     }
5488 };

5500 var DFAState = require('./../dfa/DFAState').DFAState;

5502 var getCachedPredictionContext = require('./../PredictionContext').getCachedPredictionContext;
5503 
5504 function ATNSimulator(atn, sharedContextCache) {
5505 
5506     // The context cache maps all PredictionContext objects that are ==
5507     //  to a single cached copy. This cache is shared across all contexts
5508     //  in all ATNConfigs in all DFA states.  We rebuild each ATNConfigSet
5509     //  to use only cached nodes/graphs in addDFAState(). We don't want to
5510     //  fill this during closure() since there are lots of contexts that
5511     //  pop up but are not used ever again. It also greatly slows down closure().
5512     //
5513     //  <p>This cache makes a huge difference in memory and a little bit in speed.
5514     //  For the Java grammar on java.*, it dropped the memory requirements
5515     //  at the end from 25M to 16M. We don't store any of the full context
5516     //  graphs in the DFA because they are limited to local context only,
5517     //  but apparently there's a lot of repetition there as well. We optimize
5518     //  the config contexts before storing the config set in the DFA states
5519     //  by literally rebuilding them with cached subgraphs only.</p>
5520     //
5521     //  <p>I tried a cache for use during closure operations, that was
5522     //  whacked after each adaptivePredict(). It cost a little bit
5523     //  more time I think and doesn't save on the overall footprint
5524     //  so it's not worth the complexity.</p>
5525     ///
5526     this.atn = atn;
5527     this.sharedContextCache = sharedContextCache;
5528     return this;
5529 }
5530 
5531 // Must distinguish between missing edge and edge we know leads nowhere///
5532 ATNSimulator.ERROR = new DFAState(0x7FFFFFFF, new ATNConfigSet());
5533 
5534 
5535 ATNSimulator.prototype.getCachedContext = function(context) {
5536     if (this.sharedContextCache ===null) {
5537         return context;
5538     }
5539     var visited = {};
5540     return getCachedPredictionContext(context, this.sharedContextCache, visited);
5541 };

5545 },{"./../PredictionContext":12,"./../dfa/DFAState":35,"./ATNConfigSet":19}],23:[function(require,module,exports){
5546 //
5547 /* Copyright (c) 2012-2017 The ANTLR Project. All rights reserved. 
5548  * Use of this file is governed by the BSD 3-clause license that 
5549  * can be found in the LICENSE.txt file in the project root. 
5550  */
5551 //
5552 
5553 // The following images show the relation of states and
5554 // {@link ATNState//transitions} for various grammar constructs.
5555 //
5556 // <ul>
5557 //
5558 // <li>Solid edges marked with an &//0949; indicate a required
5559 // {@link EpsilonTransition}.</li>
5560 //
5561 // <li>Dashed edges indicate locations where any transition derived from
5562 // {@link Transition} might appear.</li>
5563 //
5564 // <li>Dashed nodes are place holders for either a sequence of linked
5565 // {@link BasicState} states or the inclusion of a block representing a nested
5566 // construct in one of the forms below.</li>
5567 //
5568 // <li>Nodes showing multiple outgoing alternatives with a {@code ...} support
5569 // any number of alternatives (one or more). Nodes without the {@code ...} only
5570 // support the exact number of alternatives shown in the diagram.</li>
5571 //
5572 // </ul>

5615 function ATNState() {
5616     // Which ATN are we in?
5617     this.atn = null;
5618     this.stateNumber = ATNState.INVALID_STATE_NUMBER;
5619     this.stateType = null;
5620     this.ruleIndex = 0; // at runtime, we don't have Rule objects
5621     this.epsilonOnlyTransitions = false;
5622     // Track the transitions emanating from this ATN state.
5623     this.transitions = [];
5624     // Used to cache lookahead during parsing, not used during construction
5625     this.nextTokenWithinRule = null;
5626     return this;
5627 }

5666     if (other instanceof ATNState) {
5667         return this.stateNumber===other.stateNumber;
5668     } else {
5669         return false;
5670     }

5674     return false;
5675 };

5678 ATNState.prototype.addTransition = function(trans, index) {
5679 	if(index===undefined) {
5680 		index = -1;
5681 	}
5682     if (this.transitions.length===0) {
5683         this.epsilonOnlyTransitions = trans.isEpsilon;
5684     } else if(this.epsilonOnlyTransitions !== trans.isEpsilon) {
5685         this.epsilonOnlyTransitions = false;
5686     }
5687     if (index===-1) {
5688         this.transitions.push(trans);
5689     } else {
5690         this.transitions.splice(index, 1, trans);
5691     }
5692 };
